Week 12 Scatter Plot

Anindiatie Parastikasari and Sekar Ramadhani

6/9/2021

A Scatterplot displays the relationship between 2 numeric variables. Each dot represents an observation. Their position on the X (horizontal) and Y (vertical) axis represents the values of the 2 variables.

Case Study 1

summary(faithful)
##    eruptions        waiting    
##  Min.   :1.600   Min.   :43.0  
##  1st Qu.:2.163   1st Qu.:58.0  
##  Median :4.000   Median :76.0  
##  Mean   :3.488   Mean   :70.9  
##  3rd Qu.:4.454   3rd Qu.:82.0  
##  Max.   :5.100   Max.   :96.0

Problem

Find the scatter plot of the eruption durations and waiting intervals in faithful. Does it reveal any relationship between the variables?

  filter(continent=="Asia") %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarize(mean(lifeExp), mean(gdp))
